          {
            "t": "text",
            "content": "Horchata is a sweet, creamy drink with roots in Spain and Latin America. Traditions vary by region — some use rice, others tiger nuts or seeds — but the result is always refreshing and festive.",
            "role": "body",
            "tone": "surface"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "content": "Our version starts with Carolina Gold Rice Middlins from Marsh Hen Mill — a heirloom rice that lends a subtle nuttiness and silky texture to every sip.",
            "role": "body",
            "tone": "surface"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "content": "Soak the rice with cinnamon, blend until smooth, sweeten to taste, and serve over ice. It's the kind of drink that turns an ordinary afternoon into a celebration.",
            "role": "body",
            "tone": "surface"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "content": "Whether you're hosting a holiday gathering or cooling off after a summer meal, horchata is a crowd-pleaser that pairs beautifully with Southern classics.",
            "role": "body",
            "tone": "surface"
